# Custom Domain Configuration for GitHub Pages
# ============================================
# 
# To use a custom domain with GitHub Pages:
# 
# 1. Replace this entire file with your domain name only:
#    example.com
#    or
#    www.example.com
# 
# 2. Configure DNS with your domain provider:
# 
#    For apex domain (example.com):
#    Type: A
#    Name: @
#    Value: 185.199.108.153
#    TTL: 3600
#    
#    (Repeat for these IPs:)
#    185.199.109.153
#    185.199.110.153
#    185.199.111.153
# 
#    For subdomain (www.example.com):
#    Type: CNAME
#    Name: www
#    Value: yourusername.github.io
#    TTL: 3600
# 
# 3. In GitHub: Settings → Pages → Custom domain
#    Enter your domain and save
# 
# 4. Check "Enforce HTTPS" after DNS propagates
# 
# Leave this file as-is to use GitHub Pages subdomain:
# yourusername.github.io/virtual-tourist-virtual/
